.SH "NAME"
pixhalve \- halve a color pix file
.SH "SYNOPSIS"
.sp
\fBpixhalve\fP [\-a] [\-s \fIsquareinsize\fP] [\-w \fIin_width\fP] [\-n \fIin_height\fP] [<] [\fIinfile.pix\fP] > \fIoutfile.pix\fP
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
.sp
\fBpixhalve\fP will take a color \fBpix\fP(5) format
file of given dimensions and reduce the resolution of the file by one
half in each direction using a 5x5 pyramid filter.  If a file name is
not given, standard input will be used. The \fB\-w\fP and \fB\-n\fP
flags specify the input file width and number of scan lines in pixels;
they can be set to the same value via \fB\-s\fP. Defaults of 512 are
assumed for unspecified dimensions.
.sp
The \fB\-a\fP flag indicates autosizing (off by default).
